2026-04-19T12:03:04.933Z JOY-00F1-AD comment.added "Plan:\n\n1. Core: add joy_core::model::project::validate_acronym(value) -> Result<(), String>. Rules: uppercase ASCII alphanumeric (A-Z, 0-9), must start with a letter, length 2-8. Matches the shape of all existing project acronyms in the Joyint ecosystem (JI, JOT, JOY, JISITE, JAPP ...).\n\n2. Core: unit tests for validate_acronym covering accept (JYN, JOT, JI, JAPP, JISITE, JX2) and reject (empty, single char, 9+ chars, lowercase, leading digit, hyphen, whitespace, non-ASCII, starts-with-digit).\n\n3. CLI: in joy-cli/src/commands/project.rs set_value, replace the current bail for 'acronym' with a set-path that calls validate_acronym, assigns project.acronym. 'created' stays read-only.\n\n4. CLI: update help text on the Set subcommand doc comment and the --help string to list 'acronym' among settable keys.\n\n5. CLI: after set_value succeeds in run(), if key == 'acronym', print an explicit note that existing item IDs keep their previous prefix and only new items use the new prefix. Prevents user surprise (ADR-adjacent policy decision we accepted for the jot -> jyn rename).\n\n6. cargo fmt, cargo clippy --workspace -D warnings, cargo test --workspace.\n\n7. Commit on branch rename/jyn with conventional commit 'feat(cli): allow joy project set acronym' referencing JOY-00F1-AD. Include the staged JOY-00F1-AD item YAML.\n\n8. joy submit for review.\n\nNon-goals for this item: validating acronym at init time (separate scope), renaming existing items (user chose historical preservation), retroactively re-prefixing." [ai:claude@joy delegated-by:horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
