2026-04-19T12:15:07.227Z JOY-00F1-AD comment.added "[x] Implemented on branch rename/jyn, commit d034322.\n\n- Added joy_core::model::project::validate_acronym with 7 unit tests covering real project acronyms (JI/JOT/JOY/JON/JP/JAPP/JOYC/JISITE), alphanumeric inputs (V2, A1B2), case + whitespace normalization, and rejection of too-short, too-long, non-alnum, non-ASCII inputs.\n- joy-cli project.rs: set_value now accepts 'acronym', validates via validate_acronym, stores the normalized form. 'created' stays read-only separately.\n- run() prints a two-line note after an acronym change: existing items keep their previous prefix, only new items use the new prefix.\n- Updated Set subcommand doc comment to list acronym among settable keys.\n- cargo fmt, cargo clippy --workspace -- -D warnings (CI shape), just test-unit (243/243), just test-cmd (2/2) all green.\n\nUnrelated finding, out of scope: cargo clippy --all-targets surfaces two pre-existing errors in crates/joy-core/src/guard.rs:385 (clone_on_copy) and one expect_fun_call elsewhere. Only under --all-targets, CI uses --workspace without --all-targets so it does not fail. Worth a cleanup item at some point but not here." [ai:claude@joy delegated-by:horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
