2026-04-19T20:02:12.288Z JOY-00F4-CF comment.added "Additional manifestation of the same divergence, observed in the wild:\n\n  $ joy auth status\n  No active session for horst.schwarz@joydev.com. Run `joy auth` to authenticate.\n\n  $ joy project member\n    Member                   Auth con pln ...\n    horst.schwarz@joydev.com ✓ 🔐  ...\n\nT1 authed at an earlier TTY, T2 is a different TTY (second terminal of the same OS user). T2's `joy auth status` correctly returns "no active session" (check_session enforces claims.tty == current_tty for human members). `joy project member` however shows the check mark for horst - member_auth_status only validates signature + TTL + member match on the session file, it does NOT run the TTY check.\n\nTwo user-visible states that disagree in the same shell at the same moment. Fixing member_auth_status for humans means either:\n- run the same TTY check as check_session, OR\n- introduce a distinct display state (for example "session file present, not usable in this shell") so the divergence is visible rather than hidden.\n\nParallel AI case holds too: if JOY_SESSION env is missing in this shell, resolve_identity refuses to act as the AI, but member_auth_status still shows the AI check mark because the file is intact.\n\nThe bug therefore spans both member paths; the fix is one mechanism (align member_auth_status with resolve_identity's actual preconditions), applied for humans and AIs." [ai:claude@joy delegated-by:horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
